The Presidential Commission on Good Government, the agency tasked to recover the ill-gotten wealth taken during the dictatorship of Ferdinand Marcos has submitted plans to President Benigno Aquino III to end its operations after 27 years. (Business World) (Rappler)Iran's former nuclear negotiator Hassan Rouhani enters the race to succeed President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad, accusing the incumbent of needlessly incurring crippling economic sanctions. (Al Jazeera)